{"id":"hold","term":"Hold","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>A fortress, the name given to David’s lurking-places (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Samuel 22:4\">1 Sam. 22:4</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 1:5\">5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 24:22\">24:22</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Samuel 22:4","Genesis 1:5","Genesis 24:22"]}